    "body": "First why are you using shell to install **starship** on **MacOS** ? Why aren't you using **brew** ?\n\nFor your error, it says that **it can't find  the `/usr/local/bin` directory**.\n\nYou are using a beta version, usually that `/usr/local/bin` already exists on **MacOS** !\n\nTry to run command on your terminal emulator(Terminal, iTerm ...) to check if directory already exists:\n```sh\n$ ls /usr/local/bin\n```\nOtherwise: \n1. Download the tar file, extract it, look for **starship** bin\n2. add it to your `$PATH` in your **.zshrc** file:\n```zsh\nexport PATH=\"/path/to/starship/bin:$PATH\"\n```\n3. Source your **.zshrc**\n```sh\n$ source ~/.zshrc\n```\n4. Check that starship bin has been added to `$PATH`:\n```sh\n$ which starship\n```\nYou should see something like `/path/to/starship/bin/starship`\n5. Init starship at your **.zshrc** file:\n```zsh\n# add this line after the export PATH\neval \"$(starship init zsh)\"\n```\n6. Re-source **.zshrc** file:\n```sh\n$ source ~/.zshrc\n```",
