    "updated_at": "2026-01-01T13:53:43Z",
    "body": "This seems like a valid issue. On Apple Silicon Macs, `/usr/local/bin` doesn't exist by default (it was typically created by Homebrew on Intel Macs, and Homebrew now uses `/opt/homebrew` on Apple Silicon).\n\nI looked at how other tools handle this:\n\n| Tool | Default install path | \n|------|---------------------|\n| Deno | `~/.deno/bin` | \n| fnm | `~/.fnm` or `~/.local/share/fnm` | \n| Rust | `~/.cargo/bin` | \n\nThey all install to home directory to avoid permission issues and auto-create the directory if needed.\n\n@starship/mission-control What do you think about changing the default to something like `~/.starship/bin`? Note that this would require users to add it to their PATH since it's not in PATH by default.\n\nOr should we just add logic to create `/usr/local/bin` if it doesn't exist (with confirmation)?",
